GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_FrictionFailure> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_FrictionFailure> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#FrictionFailure> ;
    narr:childCount "44"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "cfcb3bea7a76d348360a7e3dd14606bd1b4671b6" ;
    narr:narration """This hub tracks the friction points in AI adoption, development, and sales. Development friction is dominated by [AI code back-pressure](narr:Narrative_AIBackPressureCodeReview), where generation speed outpaces human review, and the [AI action trap](narr:Narrative_AIActionTrap), an infinite loop of ungrounded execution. These technical hurdles are compounded by [technical adoption friction](narr:Narrative_TechnicalAdoptionFriction), where users fear workflow contamination, and [identity onboarding gaps](narr:Narrative_IdentityOnboardingGap) that leave agents ungrounded. Sales and adoption are hindered by the [activation gap](narr:Narrative_ActivationGap), where the product is misperceived as an investment rather than an immediate tool, and [two-sided legibility problems](narr:Narrative_TwoSidedLegibilityProblem) that prevent practitioners from communicating their methodology. Organizational memory failures, such as [context hemorrhage](narr:Narrative_ContextHemorrhage) and [day-to-day re-litigation](narr:Narrative_DayToDayRelitigation), highlight the structural [forgetting bottleneck](narr:Narrative_ForgettingBottleneckIsRole) inherent in decision-junction roles. While [value is proven by showing](narr:Narrative_ShowVsDemoProof), the path to scale remains blocked by [internal organizational conflict](narr:Narrative_StaffingAIAdoptionWall) and the need for [ambient adoption](narr:Position_AmbientAdoption) beyond developer tooling.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_AIActionTrap> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_AIBackPressureCodeReview> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ActivationGap> ;
